    • Field Detail

      • start

        public final int start
        Start index where measurments are taken from sensor signal. This attribute is defined on instantiation and can not be modified.
        Since:
        0.1

      • end

        public final int end
        End index where measurements are taken from sensor signal. This attribute is defined on instantiation and can not be modified.
        Since:
        0.1

      • step

        public final int step
        Number of signal steps between measure points.
        Since:
        0.1

      • values

        public final float[] values
        Signal spectrum values. These are the core values that represent the sensor reading. The first one at [0] references to the start index within the spectrum, whereas the following ones are measured with an interval of step.

      • time

        public final long time
        Timestamp when signal was received.

    • Constructor Detail

      • TactSpectrum

        public TactSpectrum(long time,
                    float[] values,
                    int start,
                    int step)
        Creates a new TactSpectrum instance. This will hold a Tact value set (signal spectrum) which has been received at a specific point in time.
        Parameters:
        time - the point in time when the value set has been received/recorded as long (UNIX stamp).
        values - of signal as float array .
        start - index where measures have been taken from.
        step - width between signal values.
        Since:
        0.1

      • bias

        public float bias()
        Signal bias, relative position of signal maximum in spectrum. This value will be 0 if max is located at signal start index, and can reach 1 if located at the end of value list.
        Returns:
        Relative position of maxima within values list as float.

      • peak

        public float peak()
        Signal peak, realative amplitude of signal maximum in spectrum.
        Returns:
        Relative amplitude of maxima within values list as float.

      • maxAt

        public int maxAt()
        Spectrum index where signal maximum is present. This index referes to the location of the value within the values array. To determine the absolute signal index: add maxAt() times step to the start index.
        Returns:
        Position of the signal maximum within the values array as int.
        Since:
        0.1

      • minAt

        public int minAt()
        Spectrum index where signal minimum is present. This index refers to the location of the value within the values array. To determine the absolte signal index: add minAt() times step to the start index. 
         int sigMinIndex = start + minAt() * step;
        Returns:
        Position of the signal minimum within the values array as int.
        Since:
        0.1

      • smooth

        public float[] smooth()

      • bins

        public float[] bins(int resolution)
        Groups signal spectrum into bins. The number of bins must be power of two and shall not exceede the number of actual values.
        Parameters:
        resolution - number of groups. Power of two integer value; not exceeding spectrum values length.
        Returns:
        signal spectrum grouped into bins as list of float values.
        Since:
        0.1
